This section contains the full changelog of **Doxee Platform&reg;**** release 6.7**. This release introduced major enhancements to several components of the Doxee Platform&reg;. Please refer to the respective sections for a complete overview of changes.

Before adopting this software version, please read these release notes carefully to find out about new features, improvements, changes, fixes, deprecations, known bugs, limitations, or user impacts which may affect your operations.

- [Business Designer: Complete UX redesign](/doxee-platform/docs/release-notes-i-edition-6-7#business-designer-complete-ux-redesign)

- [Template Designer, Business Designer and Composer: New interactive Form Fields feature](/doxee-platform/docs/release-notes-i-edition-6-7#template-designer-business-designer-and-composer-new-interactive-form-fields-feature)

- [Composer: New accessibility mode with full WCAG compliance](/doxee-platform/docs/release-notes-i-edition-6-7#composer-new-accessibility-mode-with-full-wcag-compliance)

- [Workplace 2: More Human Tasks and new customisation options](/doxee-platform/docs/release-notes-i-edition-6-7#workplace-2-more-human-tasks-and-new-customisation-options)

- [Workplace 2 and Human Tasks: Third-party integration with CRM apps](/doxee-platform/docs/release-notes-i-edition-6-7#workplace-2-and-human-tasks-thirdparty-integration-with-crm-apps)

## What’s new in 6.7
### Business Designer: Complete UX redesign
We’ve updated Business Designer with a completely **refreshed user interface**, designed to improve usability and user experience while keeping all existing functionalities intact. The new layout organizes common actions more logically, aligning with modern design standards to make navigation more intuitive.

![](data:image/png;base64,)New user interface of Business Designer

The left sidebar has been redesigned to accommodate all general configuration views, while the right sidebar now houses setting options that are specific to the selected view or element. The preview options and page view settings are now logically grouped with the file saving actions in the top toolbar, following established UX conventions. All other existing functions and interfaces have been kept intact.

### Template Designer, Business Designer and Composer: New interactive Form Fields feature
Form Fields let you create interactive form documents. The fields can be made to interact with each other dynamically depending on the selection. The template creator can configure predefined selection options and the underlying XPath expression-based logic between form interactions — for example, a particular value in a form field may add more form fields further down, or change some content elsewhere in the document.

Form Fields, their logic and properties can be configured in a new, dedicated view in Business Designer and Template Designer. In Composer, the new tab Form Fields in the sidebar helps users keep an overview of all available fields in the document.

![](data:image/png;base64,)Form Fields view in Business Designer

The new Form Field feature replaces and expands the legacy JavaScript logic from the previous Composer application with a transparent, maintainable, and user-accessible configuration model. It enables both technical and semi-technical users to model complex behaviour in a visual environment without needing to write code.

### Composer: New accessibility mode with full WCAG compliance
Composer is now fully WCAG-compliant and universally accessible with assistive technology and alternative navigational methods. The updated design adheres to the latest accessibility standards, making Composer more inclusive and easier to use for everyone — regardless of ability.

While the functionality remains the same, the new theme improves readability and navigation with button labels, providing a seamless experience for all users.

![](data:image/png;base64,)WCAG theme in Composer

### Workplace 2: More Human Tasks and new customisation options
The list of available Human Tasks has been expanded with Generic Search, Excel Input, and Data List. New configuration options allow to control the position, text and direction of navigation buttons, as well as the localisation depending on the language setting of the application. These additions further expand the scenarios and possibilities that can be covered by a Business Case.

null

Additionally, the navigation buttons now support dynamic localisation depending on the current language setting of Workplace 2. Business Case creators can do this by adding a language attribute and specifying the correct string to be used for each language.

null

Furthermore, it’s now possible to control which steps will be displayed in the sidebar when a Business Case Instance is opened. For example, Business Case creators can choose to hide the progress labels until a certain point in the Business Case is reached. This upgrade expands the customisation capabilities of the Worplace 2 application significantly, and provides coverage for highly specific use cases.

null

### Workplace 2 and Human Tasks: Third-party integration with CRM apps
Workplace 2 now supports direct integration with leading CRM platforms, including Salesforce and SAP. This allows you to embed the application directly into your CRM workflow, streamlining content creation and management without switching tools.

Control which modules are visible within the CRM system with customizable configuration options, tailoring the experience to fit specific needs.

null

## Changelog of 6.7
### Doxee Platform&reg;
> Actions required before installing this version

- The storage format has changed. It’s recommended to export storages with Storage Manager, run the export through the Migrator, and reimport the migrated storages.

- Task queries have been changed and must be adjusted.

- **Added **support for OIDC confidential client login for technical access.

- **Fixed** DnfQueryBuilder incorrectly handling nested and/and/or structures. Queries like `and(and(or(a, and(b, b))))` were incorrectly transformed into `and(a, b, c)` by DnfQueryBuilder.

- **Improved:** Replaced Task Manager queries with a generic Query API.

- **Improved **the Resource Access Layer (RAL) to handle date-time properties that don’t contain milliseconds.

- **Fixe****d** vulnerabilities by upgrading libraries:

activemq-client to 6.1.6

- activemq-client-openwire-legacy to 6.1.6

- commons-lang3 to 3.18.0

- jackson to 2.20.1

- jackson-annotations to 2.20

- jaxb-core to 4.0.5

- jersey to 3.1.11

- netty-codec-http2 to 4.1.124.Final

- netty-codec-http to 4.1.125.Final

- netty-codec to 4.1.125.Final

- nimbus-oauth to 11.30.1

- netty to 4.2.7.Final

- undertow-core to 2.3.20.Final

### Business Designer
> Backward compatibility

Please note that the user right `RIGHT_V_EXTERNAL_RESOURCES_MANAGEMENT` has been renamed to `RIGHT_V_EXTERNAL_RESOURCES`.

The user role `ROLE_BUSINESS_USER` also received new user rights:

- `RIGHT_E_FORMS` 

- `RIGHT_V_GLOBAL_FORM_FIELDS`

- `RIGHT_O_CREATE_GLOBAL_FORM_FIELDS_PACKAGE`

- **Added **interactive Form Fields, which can be used to create fillable form documents. Template creators can add and configure fillable fields with predefined content options, which can optionally be made to interact with each other. For example, they can change which fields are mandatory based on the value selected for a drop-down form field. Form Fields can be filled with actual values in the Composer application. 

- **Added **editability support for Same-Time Positioned Content (STPC) in the Business Designer editor, if that content has been set as editable by the template creator. Double-clicking in the header, footer or side sections of the page opens them up for editing.

- **Added** support for Instream Foreign Object elements, which can be used for inline graphics or other generic objects. It can contain expression attributes similar to dynamic value expressions, or child elements (XSL code).

- **Added **functional support for inline block containers, which allow placing block elements alongside text and other inline elements. itx:inline-block-container corresponds to the fo:inline-container element.

- **Added** support for the XSL Code element, which allows to add XSLT snippets to templates. This is a feature consolidation from Template Designer.

- **Added** support for the Apply Templates element. This element allows to apply a referenced template to the current node or a child node. This is a feature consolidation from Template Designer.

- **Added** number formatting logic.

- **Improved:** Complex page masters can now use simple page masters. This is a feature consolidation from Template Designer.

- **Improved** the entire user interface of the Business Designer application with a complete redesign that streamlines the existing surfaces and functions.

- **Improved** the filepicker window to support copy, cut and paste actions on files and folders.

- **Improved** tables to support reordering of columns and rows with drag-and-drop in the Outline.

> Limitations

Using this action on complex tables may lead to unexpected results.

- **Fixed:** The Problems &amp; Events tab was displaying non-existent errors. This issue occurred when a block Template Part was present in an Insertion Point as a chosen Template Part.

- **Fixed** unresponsive clicking behaviour when selecting text input fields with the mouse.

- **Fixed** erratic clicking behavior when trying to open the preview drop-down menu to change the preview format. This bug caused every other click to trigger the preview itself, instead.

- **Fixed** failing PDF and Composer previews.

- **Fixed** broken text search in the filepicker.

- **Fixed** broken focus when renaming a file through the filepicker.

- **Fixed:** The *Save as* action caused a soft lock of the entire application.

- **Fixed** a bug that caused errors in PDF preview if there were base64-encoded dynamic images present in the template.

- **Fixed** incorrect positioning and overflowing of tooltips and the floating toolbar throughout the application.

### Composer
- **Added** support for user comments within the template editor. Composer users can add comments attached to a specific location in the document or general comments attached to the document as a whole. Comment indicators along the edge of the document page show where a comment has been left, and can be activated or deactivated in the page view settings. All comments can be viewed in the new, dedicated Comments tab in the right sidebar.

- **Added **interactive Form Fields, which can be used to create fillable form documents. Composer users can fill the fields with predefined content, which may influence other form fields based on the underlying logic. A new, dedicated Form Fields tab in the right sidebar gives a complete overview of all form fields that are present in the current document. The new Form Field feature replaces and expands the legacy JavaScript logic from the previous Composer application with a transparent, maintainable, and user-accessible configuration model. It enables both technical and semi-technical users to model complex behaviour in a visual environment without needing to write code.

- **Added **editability support for static page content in the Composer editor, if that content has been set as editable by the template creator. Double-clicking in the header, footer or side sections of the page opens them up for editing.

- **Added **functional support for inline block containers, which allow placing block elements alongside text and other inline elements. itx:inline-block-container corresponds to the fo:inline-container element.

- **Improved **accessibility features in Compose, improving usability for screen readers and ensuring access for all users.

- **Improved:** The Composer Human Task now inherits the language setting of the Workplace application.

- **Improved **the Composer Human Task to support refreshing XML data, for example in Refreshables.

- **Fixed **Insertion Points being incorrectly colour-coded as nested (orange) in the Insertion Point indicator along the sides of a document page.

- **Fixed **unwanted scrolling behaviour when clicking in the Insertion Points &gt; Available tab.

- **Fixed** unresponsive toggle behaviour in the application.

- **Fixed** incorrect positioning and overflowing of tooltips throughout the application.

- **Fixed** a visual bug that caused a white box to appear on the page. This issue occurred after inserting an element through the right-click context menu action.

- **Fixed** a visual bug that sometimes caused a red arrow to appear next to the floating toolbar.

- **Fixed** unresponsive text resizing in the Help tab.

- **Fixed:** Composer didn’t recognise test data in documents created with Template Designer. It was identified that the filepicker logic of Composer only processes test data when opening documents with the filepicker, not when opening documents directly through links.

- **Fixed** an XSL runtime error that resulted in errors in loading documents in Composer.

- **Fixed:** Relative paths to images were being resolved incorrectly. This issue occurred when the document was opened from the pipeline by the Composer Human Task.

- **Fixed **an issue due to which the Composer Human Task didn’t replace the XML entities in the output parameter `xmlOutputData`. This caused the Human Task to produce invalid XMLs.

### Process Engine
- **Added **the new activity `PdfBoxFormCreator` for creating PDF forms. This new activity replaces the previous `PdfFormCreator` activity and supports newer PDF versions. The previous activity has been deprecated.

- **Fixed:** The instantiation of processes failed when setting up an OpenID or Salesforce Process Engine.

- **Fixed:** The activity `readPrincipals` was incorrectly requiring a technical user ID.

- **Fixed** TechnicalCredentialsManager logging debug messages on WARN. This caused the log to fill up rapidly.

- **Fixed: **When deleting volatile processes from the Process Engine storage, for example during startup and shutdown, only instances with the ID prefix `pv~` were deleted. The expected behaviour is also to delete all volatile processes (prefixed with `*v~`).

- **Fixed:** When finding a volatile process instance in the storage that is unknown to the proxy storage, the proxy returns null as part of the search result. The expected behaviour is to return the actual process instance. Additionally, volatile process instances are expected to be known to the proxy storage - this issue was fixed separately.

- **Fixed:** Calling the Query API `disposeProcesses` endpoint without a query incorrectly transformed a null reply as true, meaning that all processes were disposed. The expected behaviour is to return an exception when `disposeProcesses` is called without a query.

- **Fixed:** The thread pool configuration for service processes was being ignored. This issue occurred both for the globally set default, as well as individual service configurations.

### Task Manager
- **Improved:** Replaced Task Manager queries with a generic Query API. This is the same API that is being used by the Process Engine.

- **Improved:** The Task Manager Query API can be used to terminate multiple tasks.

- **Improved:** Tasks can no longer be checked out by all authenticated users for other users. This action is now restricted to supervisors and admins.

### Template Designer
- **Added **interactive Form Fields, which can be used to create fillable form documents. Template creators can add and configure fillable fields with predefined content options, which can optionally be made to interact with each other. For example, they can change which fields are mandatory based on the value selected for a drop-down form field. Form Fields can be filled with actual values in the Composer application. The new Form Field feature replaces and expands the legacy JavaScript logic with a transparent, maintainable, and user-accessible configuration model. It enables both technical and semi-technical users to model complex behaviour in a visual environment without needing to write code.

- **Fixed **an issue that caused errors when adding indexing dependencies to the Dependency Analyzer.

- **Fixed** a bug that caused rendering errors for templates with images, text fields, or text areas.

### Workplace 1
> This section refers to changes made to the **Workplace 1** application.

- **Improved:** Replaced Task Manager queries with a generic Query API.

### Workplace 2
> This section refers to changes made to the **Workplace 2** application.

- **Added** support for full or partial integration of Workplace 2 in third-party CRM applications. The integration is modular and fully configurable.

- **Added** the Generic Search Human Task. This Human Task allows Workplace administrators to set up a search process and configure which fields can be used by Workplace 2 users. This is a feature consolidation from Workplace 1.

- **Added **the Excel Input Human Task. Business Case creators can specify which Excel file should be used and can add a text description. The file will be displayed as HTML in the Human Task and can be saved by Business Users to the repository. Formulas are fully retained.

- **Added** the Data List Human Task, which allows to display data from an external data source, for example a database query in a previous process step. The results are displayed in a sortable list.

- **Added** extensive customisation options for the Workplace 2 interface, including branding and labels.

- **Added **the option to switch the user interface to a dark theme for viewing comfort.

- **Added** extensive customisation options for Human Task interfaces. Workplace administrators can now configure the look and position of navigation buttons.

- **Improved** the File List Human Task with added sorting and file preview abilities.

- **Improved:** The Composer Human Task now inherits the language setting of the Workplace application.

- **Improved **the Composer Human Task to support refreshing XML data, for example in Refreshables.

- **Improved **the Composer Human Task to support multiple document templates.

- **Improved** the Composer Human Task to save changes made to a document. To use this feature, exit the Human Task with the **Exit** button and select the option *Unlock the task and save changes* in the pop-up window.

> Limitations

Due to technical limitations, this functionality only applies to cases with a single Composer template. Multi-template Composer Human Tasks must be finished in order to save the edits made to them.

- **Improved** the way blocked users are displayed in the Business Case details. This field will now only be displayed if there are blocked users. If there are no blocked users, the field won’t be displayed in the details page.

- **Improved:** Set search filters are now displayed above the table header row, giving the user a clear view of which parameters are being filtered.

- **Improved:** Business Cases can now be launched with HTTP requests.

- **Improved:** The Task Manager Query API can be used to terminate multiple tasks.

- **Improved** the details page of Business Cases to display the Business Case ID.

- **Improved:** Business Case definitions can now be downloaded from the Workplace 2 interface in XML format.

- **Fixed:** Relative paths to images were being resolved incorrectly. This issue occurred when the document was opened from the pipeline by the Composer Human Task.

- **Fixed **an issue due to which the Composer Human Task didn’t replace the XML entities in the output parameter `xmlOutputData`. This caused the Human Task to produce invalid XMLs.

- **Fixed** overly long folder breadcrumbs being cut off on mobile devices.

- **Fixed:** The Problems &amp; Events window wasn’t being refreshed dynamically. Users had to trigger a page refresh to view new entries. Additionally, setting a filter for which no entries exist cleared the window completely, necessitating a page refresh.

- **Fixed** a visual bug due to which not all table columns were visually marked as selected (blue) during a multi-select action.

- **Fixed:** User selection in the *Records per page* drop-down menu at the bottom of tables wasn’t being persisted when the user switched to another page.

- **Fixed** a bug that caused the browser tab name to always display the name of the first Human Task in a Business Case. The expected behaviour is for the browser tab to always display the current Human Task label.

- **Fixed:** Newly created folders would display the contents of the root folder as well.

- **Fixed** login issues in Chromium-based web browsers. The application was sometimes soft-locked in an endless loading screen after entering the credentials.

- **Fixed:** Email Human Task was incorrectly substituting spaces with non-breaking spaces (&amp;nbsp;), leading to incorrect line breaks in Outlook.

- **Fixed** excessive whitespace between input fields in the Email Human Task.

- **Fixed:** The *Recently opened* section in the dashboard wasn’t being updated dynamically.

- **Fixed**: Opening the Business Case details called the backend API endpoint multiple times. The expected behaviour is to call the endpoint only once.

- **Fixed:** File List Human Task was unable to resolve relative URL paths, leading to a 404 error.

- **Fixed:** HTML Human Task didn’t correctly copy the input parameters to the output.

- **Fixed:** Summary Human Task showed an empty page when only one entry was configured in the XML.

- **Fixed** search filters causing breaking issues when no results could be found. These issues occurred in the Tasks tab.
